explanation: Binary search is used to find the optimal value. The search range is from 0 to 10^5. For each mid value, the sum of the array when all numbers larger than mid are changed to mid is calculated. The optimal value is the one that makes this sum closest to the target. In case of a tie, the smaller value is chosen.

